QorCommerce Docs (3.0) swagger 3 source

API Version 3

Authentication

API key

An API key is a special token (Qor-Client-Key) that you need to provide in header when making API calls, Like: { Qor-Client-Key: "TOKEN_VALUE" }

API key

An API key is a special token (Qor-App-Key) that you need to provide in header when making API calls, Like: { Qor-App-Key: "TOKEN_VALUE" }

Payments - Credit / Debit Cards

Purchase - Manual / Keyed Entry (eComm)

Process a payment with a keyed/manually entered credit/debit card


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/sale/manual/ Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "creditcard": "",
        "cvv": "",
        "month": "",
        "year": "",
        "bzip": "",
        "cardfullname": "",
        "currency": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "baddress": "",
        "baddress2": "",
        "bcity": "",
        "bstate": "",
        "bcountry": "",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "store_card": false
    }
}
  • transaction_data * undefined
200

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Card Sale processed successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_approved": "15.00",
    "authcode": "606012",
    "token": "909055$DQs7OHDo"
}
  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved`, `declined` and `error` Example: approved
  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail Example: GW00
  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message Example: Card Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time the transaction has taken place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when requesting voids and refunds Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_approved string Description: The total amount approved and charged by the host processer Example: 15.00
  • authcode string Description: The host processor authorization code Example: 606012
  • token string Description: If the request value `store_card` = `1` then a token value representing the card will be provided in the response. This token can be stored with your customer record and used in place of a credit card for future processing Example: 909055$DQs7OHDo
cURL JavaScript Node Python 
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/sale/manual/ \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --data '{"transaction_data":{"mid":"","amount":"","creditcard":"","cvv":"","month":"","year":"","bzip":"","cardfullname":"","currency":"","invoiceid":"","orderid":"","ipaddress":"","baddress":"","baddress2":"","bcity":"","bstate":"","bcountry":"","cfirstname":"","clastname":"","cemail":"","cphone":"","store_card":false}}'
fetch('https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/sale/manual/', { 
    method: 'POST', 
    headers: {
        "Qor-App-Key": "T6554252567241061980",
        "Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82"
    }, 
    body: {
        "transaction_data": {
            "mid": "",
            "amount": "",
            "creditcard": "",
            "cvv": "",
            "month": "",
            "year": "",
            "bzip": "",
            "cardfullname": "",
            "currency": "",
            "invoiceid": "",
            "orderid": "",
            "ipaddress": "",
            "baddress": "",
            "baddress2": "",
            "bcity": "",
            "bstate": "",
            "bcountry": "",
            "cfirstname": "",
            "clastname": "",
            "cemail": "",
            "cphone": "",
            "store_card": false
        }
    }, 
}) 
.then(e => e.json()) 
.then((data) => { 
    console.log('Request succeeded with JSON response', data); 
}) 
.catch((error) => { 
    console.log('Request failed', error); 
});
const request = require('request');
 
const options = { 
    method: 'POST', 
    url: 'https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/sale/manual/', 
    headers: {"Qor-App-Key": "T6554252567241061980","Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82"}, 
    body: {
        "transaction_data": {
            "mid": "",
            "amount": "",
            "creditcard": "",
            "cvv": "",
            "month": "",
            "year": "",
            "bzip": "",
            "cardfullname": "",
            "currency": "",
            "invoiceid": "",
            "orderid": "",
            "ipaddress": "",
            "baddress": "",
            "baddress2": "",
            "bcity": "",
            "bstate": "",
            "bcountry": "",
            "cfirstname": "",
            "clastname": "",
            "cemail": "",
            "cphone": "",
            "store_card": false
        }
    }, 
};
 
request(options, function (error, response, body) { 
    if (error) throw new Error(error);
 
    console.log(body); 
});
import requests

url = "https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/sale/manual/"

headers = {
    "Qor-App-Key": "T6554252567241061980",
    "Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82"
}

body = {
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "creditcard": "",
        "cvv": "",
        "month": "",
        "year": "",
        "bzip": "",
        "cardfullname": "",
        "currency": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "baddress": "",
        "baddress2": "",
        "bcity": "",
        "bstate": "",
        "bcountry": "",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "store_card": false
    }
}

response = requests.POST(url, headers=headers, body=body)

  • Response
  • Coding

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

Purchase - Use a Payment Token

Process a sale with a card token


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/sale/token Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "creditcard": "",
        "currency": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": ""
    }
}
  • transaction_data * object
    • mid string
    • amount * string
    • service_charge string
    • creditcard * string Description: the card token
    • cvv * string
    • currency string
    • invoiceid string
    • orderid * string
    • ipaddress string
    • cfirstname string
    • clastname string
    • cemail string
    • cphone string
    • risk_score integer
    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
200

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Card Sale processed successfully",

    "amount_approved": "15.00",

  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message Example: Card Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time the transaction has taken place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55

Purchase - Use Level 2 or 3 Transaction Data

Process a payment with Level 2 or 3 data


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/sale/lvl2_3 Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {
        "islvl3": true,
        "mid": "<>",
        "amount": "required",
        "creditcard": "required",
        "cvv": "required",
        "month": "required",
        "year": "required",
        "bzip": "required",
        "cardfullname": "required if store_card==true",
        "currency": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "baddress": "",
        "baddress2": "",
        "bcity": "",
        "bstate": "",
        "bcountry": "",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "tax_amount": 0,
        "purchase_order": "",
        "shipping_zip": "",
        "shipping_country": "",
        "items": [
            {
                "name": "",
                "description": "",
                "ucc": " ",
                "upc": "",
                "unit_price": 0,
                "units_sold": 0,
                "unit_measurement": "",
                "total_amount": ""
            },
            {
                "name": "",
                "description": "",
                "ucc": " ",
                "upc": "",
                "unit_price": 0,
                "units_sold": 0,
                "unit_measurement": "",
                "total_amount": ""
            }
        ]
    }
}
  • transaction_data object
    • islvl3 boolean
    • mid string
    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
    • amount string
    • creditcard string
    • cvv string
    • month string
    • year string
    • bzip string
    • cardfullname string
    • currency string
    • invoiceid string
    • orderid string
    • ipaddress string
    • baddress string
    • baddress2 string
    • bcity string
    • bstate string
    • bcountry string
    • cfirstname string
    • clastname string
    • cemail string
    • cphone string
    • tax_amount integer
    • purchase_order string
    • shipping_zip string
    • shipping_country string
      • name string
      • description string
      • ucc string
      • upc string
      • unit_price integer
      • units_sold integer
      • unit_measurement string
      • total_amount string

Purchase - Use 3D Secure (3DSv2)

Process a payment with authenticated 3-D Secure information


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/sale/3ds Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "<>",
        "amount": "required",
        "creditcard": "required",
        "cvv": "required",
        "month": "required",
        "year": "required",
        "bzip": "required",
        "CAVV": "required",
        "XID": "required",
        "ECIFlag": "required",
        "cardfullname": "",
        "currency": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "baddress": "",
        "baddress2": "",
        "bcity": "",
        "bstate": "",
        "bcountry": "",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "risk_score": "",
        "store_card": 0
    }
}
  • transaction_data object
    • mid string
    • amount string
    • creditcard string
    • cvv string
    • month string
    • year string
    • bzip string
    • CAVV string
    • XID string
    • ECIFlag string
    • cardfullname string
    • currency string
    • orderid string
    • ipaddress string
    • invoiceid string
    • baddress string
    • baddress2 string
    • bcity string
    • bstate string
    • bcountry string
    • cfirstname string
    • clastname string
    • cemail string
    • cphone string
    • risk_score integer
    • store_card integer
    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
200

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Card Sale processed successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_approved": "15.00",
    "authcode": "606012",
    "token": "909055$DQs7OHDo"
}
  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved`, `declined` and `error` Example: approved
  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail Example: GW00
  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message Example: Card Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time the transaction has taken place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when requesting voids and refunds Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_approved string Description: The total amount approved and charged by the host processer Example: 15.00
  • authcode string Description: The host processor authorization code Example: 606012
  • token string Description: If the request value `store_card` = `1` then a token value representing the card will be provided in the response. This token can be stored with your customer record and used in place of a credit card for future processing Example: 909055$DQs7OHDo
cURL JavaScript Node Python 
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/sale/3ds \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --data '{"transaction_data":{"mid":"<>","amount":"required","creditcard":"required","cvv":"required","month":"required","year":"required","bzip":"required","CAVV":"required","XID":"required","ECIFlag":"required","cardfullname":"","currency":"","orderid":"","ipaddress":"","invoiceid":"","baddress":"","baddress2":"","bcity":"","bstate":"","bcountry":"","cfirstname":"","clastname":"","cemail":"","cphone":"","risk_score":"","store_card":0}}'

Recurring - Create a Recurring Purchase

Setup and process a recurring credit/debit card sale


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/recurring/setup Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "creditcard": "",
        "cvv": "",
        "month": "",
        "year": "",
        "bzip": "",
        "cardfullname": "",
        "currency": "",
        "invoiceid": "",
        "orderid": "",
        "ipaddress": "",
        "baddress": "",
        "baddress2": "",
        "bcity": "",
        "bstate": "",
        "bcountry": "",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "store_card": false
    }
}
  • transaction_data object
    • mid string Description: The merchant id (MID) assigned by <> or your merchant service provider (MSP).
    • amount string Description: the total amount to process
    • creditcard string
    • month string Description: the card expiration month - as 2 digits (ex. `02` for Febuary)
    • year string Description: the card expiration year - as 2 digits (ex. `24` for 2024)
    • cvv string Description: the credit/debit card verification value
    • bzip string Description: the customer's credit/debit card billing zip code
    • cardfullname string Description: the name printed or embossed on the front of the credit/debit card `required` if store payment is set to true
    • currency string Description: the currency to process. Defaults to `USD` if no value provided
    • orderid string Description: unique merchant order number
    • invoiceid string Description: merchant invoice number
    • ipaddress string Description: the IP address of the client or server sending the request
    • baddress string Description: the customer's billing street address
    • baddress2 string Description: the customer's billing street address 2
    • bcity string Description: the customer's billing city
    • bstate string Description: the customer's billing state code - as 2 characters (ex. FL)
    • bcountry string Description: the customer's billing country code
    • cfirstname string Description: the customer's first name
    • clastname string Description: the customer's last name
    • cemail string Description: the customer's email address
    • cphone string Description: the customer's phone number
    • store_card boolean Description: if set to `true` will store card information in the QorCommerce Vault and return a payment token
    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
200

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Card Sale processed successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_approved": "15.00",
    "authcode": "606012",
    "token": "909055$DQs7OHDo"
}
  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved`, `declined` and `error` Example: approved
  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail Example: GW00
  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message Example: Card Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time the transaction has taken place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when requesting voids and refunds Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_approved string Description: The total amount approved and charged by the host processer Example: 15.00
  • authcode string Description: The host processor authorization code Example: 606012
  • token string Description: If the request value `store_card` = `1` then a token value representing the card will be provided in the response. This token can be stored with your customer record and used in place of a credit card for future processing Example: 909055$DQs7OHDo
cURL JavaScript Node Python

  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/recurring/setup \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --data '{"transaction_data":{"mid":"","amount":"","creditcard":"","cvv":"","month":"","year":"","bzip":"","cardfullname":"","currency":"","invoiceid":"","orderid":"","ipaddress":"","baddress":"","baddress2":"","bcity":"","bstate":"","bcountry":"","cfirstname":"","clastname":"","cemail":"","cphone":"","store_card":false}}'

            "cardfullname": "",
            "currency": "",

            "bcity": "",
            "bstate": "",
            "bcountry": "",

  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message Example: Card Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time the transaction has taken place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when requesting voids and refunds Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_approved string Description: The total amount approved and charged by the host processer Example: 15.00
  • authcode string Description: The host processor authorization code Example: 606012
  • token string Description: If the request value `store_card` = `1` then a token value representing the card will be provided in the response. This token can be stored with your customer record and used in place of a credit card for future processing Example: 909055$DQs7OHDo
cURL JavaScript Node Python 
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/authorize/token \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --data '{"transaction_data":{}}'

    method: 'POST', 
    headers: {
        "Qor-App-Key": "T6554252567241061980",
        "Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82"
    },

    }, 
}) 
.then(e => e.json())

    console.log('Request succeeded with JSON response', data); 
})

    console.log('Request failed', error);

Payments - Cash

Cash (Sale)

Record a Cash sale


post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/cash Try Out

  • Request
  • Response
  • Coding

header

Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: T6554252567241061980

The unique key identifying the app making this request.

NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

string

Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "type": "",
    "mid": "",
    "transaction_data": {
        "orderid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "service_charge": "",
        "currency": "USD",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cidentity_type": "",
        "cidentity": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "ipaddress": ""
    },
    "items": [
        {
            "name": "",
            "description": "",
            "ucc": "",
            "upc": "",
            "unit_price": 0,
            "units_sold": 0,
            "unit_measurement": "",
            "total_amount": ""
        },
        {
            "name": "",
            "description": "",
            "ucc": " ",
            "upc": "",
            "unit_price": 0,
            "units_sold": 0,
            "unit_measurement": "",
            "total_amount": ""
        }
    ]
}
  • type * string
  • mid * string Description: the merchant id (MID) assigned by QorPay or your merchant service provider (MSP)
  • transaction_data * object
    • orderid * string Description: unique merchant order number
    • invoiceid string Description: merchant invoice number
    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
    • amount * string Description: the total amount collected for the sale
    • service_charge string Description: the amount of the service charge that is in the total sum of the transaction
    • currency string Description: the currency to process. Defaults to `USD` if no value provided
    • cfirstname string Description: the customer's first name
    • clastname string Description: the customer's last name
    • cidentity_type string Description: the customer's identity type. Potnetial vlaues can be `dl`, `passport`, `other`
    • cidentity string Description: the customer's identity
    • cemail string Description: the customer's email address
    • cphone string Description: the customer's phone number
    • ipaddress string Description: the IP address of the client or server sending the request
    • name string Description: the name of the item
    • description string Description: a description of the item
    • ucc string Description: the item's Universal Commercial Code
    • upc string Description: the item's Universal Product Code
    • unit_price integer Description: the price per unit for the item
    • units_sold integer Description: the number of item units sold
    • unit_measurement string Description: the unit of measurement
    • total_amount string Description: the total amount of the item sale which should equal unit_price * units_sold + any taxes, discounts and/or fees
201

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Cash Sale recorded successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_recorded": "15.00"
}
  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved` and `error` Example: approved
  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Cash Sale recorded successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time that the transaction took place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when processing refunds Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_recorded string Description: The total amount recorded Example: 15.00

**NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

body

body OPTIONAL

Example Value | Model 

{
    "transaction_data": {}
}
  • transaction_data undefined
200

Example Value | Model 

{
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "ACH Sale processed successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_approved": "15.00",
    "token": "909055$DQs7OHDo"
}
  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved`, `declined` and `error` Example: approved
  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: ACH Sale processed successfully
  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time that the transaction took place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
  • transaction_id string Description: The payment gateway unique transaction identifier. This value should be used for transaction lookups and when processing refunds and voids Example: 831649658996418
  • amount_approved string Description: The total amount approved and charged by the host processer Example: 15.00
  • token string Description: If the request value `store_accnt` = `1` then a token value representing the bank account will be provided in the response. This token can be stored with your customer record and used in place of an account for future processing. Example: 909055$DQs7OHDo

          Activate Card

          Activate a new Gift Card


          post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /gift/activate Try Out

          • Request
          • Response
          • Coding

          header

          Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

          string

          Default: T6554252567241061980

          The unique key identifying the app making this request.

          NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

          Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

          string

          Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

          The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

          **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

          body

          body OPTIONAL

          Example Value | Model 

          {
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "90655454",
        "amount": "1.5",
        "creditcard": "5544044490909090",
        "cvv": "123",
        "month": "4",
        "year": "19",
        "cardfullname": "John Smith",
        "orderid": "1233123",
        "ipaddress": "0.0.0.0",
        "currency": "USD",
        "bzip": "92838"
    }
}
          • transaction_data object
            • mid string Description: The merchant id (MID) assigned by <> or your merchant service provider (MSP).
            • amount string Description: the total amount to process
            • orderid string Description: unique merchant order number
            • invoiceid string Description: merchant invoice number
            • cvv string Description: the credit/debit card verification value
            • month string Description: the card expiration month - as 2 digits (ex. `02` for Febuary)
            • year string Description: the card expiration year - as 2 digits (ex. `24` for 2024)
            • cardfullname string Description: the name printed or embossed on the front of the credit/debit card
            • ipaddress string Description: the IP address of the client or server sending the request
            • currency string Description: the currency to process. Defaults to `USD` if no value provided
            • bzip string Description: the customer's credit/debit card billing zip code
            • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
          default

          Example Value | Model 

          {}
            cURL JavaScript Node Python 
            curl --request POST \
  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/gift/activate \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --data '{"transaction_data":{"mid":"90655454","amount":"1.5","creditcard":"5544044490909090","cvv":"123","month":"4","year":"19","cardfullname":"John Smith","orderid":"1233123","ipaddress":"0.0.0.0","currency":"USD","bzip":"92838"}}'

              Payment Tokens (tokenization)

              Create a Payment Token

              Create and store a payment token with the appropriate credit/debit card information


              post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/token Try Out

              • Request
              • Response
              • Coding

              header

              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: T6554252567241061980

              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

              The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

              **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

              body

              body OPTIONAL

              Example Value | Model 

              {
    "transaction_data": {
        "creditcard": "5544044490909090",
        "month": "04",
        "year": "19",
        "cardfullname": "John Smith",
        "baddress": "26776 Tampa Drive",
        "bcity": "Tampa",
        "bstate": "FL",
        "bzip": "33016"
    }
}
              • transaction_data * object
                • creditcard * string
                • month * string
                • year * string
                • cardfullname * string
                • baddress * string
                • bcity string
                • bstate string
                • bzip * string
              200

              Example Value | Model 

              {
    "status": " approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Get token was processed successfully",
    "token": "541341$KR0eAiX2"
}
              • status * string Description: The status of the request. Possible response values are `approved`, `declined` and `error` Example: approved
              • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
              • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Get token was processed successfully
              • token string Description: The token that was created Example: 541341$KR0eAiX2

              Update a Payment Token (exp. date)

              Update a payment token with a new expiration date


              patch https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/token Try Out

              • Request
              • Response
              • Coding

              header

              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: T6554252567241061980

              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

              The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

              **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

              body

              body OPTIONAL

              Example Value | Model 

              {
    "transaction_data": {
        "token": "541341$KR0eAiX2",
        "last4": "5413",
        "month": "02",
        "year": "25"
    }
}
              • transaction_data * object
                • token * string Description: The token to be updated Example: 541341$KR0eAiX2
                • last4 * string Description: Last 4 of the credit/debit card Example: 5413
                • month * string Description: Example: `02` (mm) Example: 02
                • year * string Description: Example: `25` (yy) Example: 25
              200

    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Update token was processed successfully",
    "token": "541341$KR0eAiX2"

              • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
              • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Update token was processed successfully
              • token string Description: The token that was updated Example: 541341$KR0eAiX2

              string

        "last4": "5413",
        "intent": ""
    }
}
              • transaction_data * object
                • token * string Description: The token to be rotated Example: 541341$KR0eAiX2
                • last4 * string Description: Last 4 of the credit/debit card or bank account number Example: 5413
                • intent string Enum: Description: Either `rotate` or `rollback` token to previous value (`rollback` can not be undone!)

              • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
              • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Rotate token was processed successfully
              • token string Description: The new token or previous token Example: 541341$KR0eAiX2

              Transactions

              Fetch a Payment Transaction

              Fetch a single payment transaction


              get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/transaction/{id} Try Out

              • Request
              • Response
              • Coding

              header

              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

              The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

              **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: T6554252567241061980

              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

              200

              Example Value | Model 

              {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": [
        {
            "trxn_status": "",
            "trxn_date": "",
            "trxn_type": "",
            "trxn_id": "",
            "payment_type": "",
            "card_type": "",
            "amount": "",
            "order_id": "",
            "authcode": "",
            "avs_code": "",
            "cv_code": "",
            "first_6": "",
            "last_4": "",
            "settled": "",
            "settled_amount": "",
            "settled_date": "",
            "ip_address": ""
        }
    ]
}
              • status * string
              • code * string
              • message * string
                • trxn_status string Description: Whether or not the tranaction was approved or delined
                • trxn_date string Description: The tranasction date and time
                • trxn_type string Description: Whether the transaction was a sale, authorization, refund or void
                • trxn_id string Description: The unique id of this the transaction
                • payment_type string Description: Whether the payment was made via `cc` (credit/debit card), `ach`, or `cash`
                • card_type string Description: The brand of the cc (if applicable)
                • amount string Description: The amount of the transaction
                • order_id string Description: The unique order id assigned to the transaction
                • authcode string Description: The authorization code of the approved transaction
                • avs_code string Description: The AVS (Address Verification Code) from the issuer for this transaction (if applicable)
                • cv_code string Description: The CVV (Card Verification Code) from the issuer for this transaction (if applicable)
                • first_6 string Description: The first six numbers of the card number or account number
                • last_4 string Description: The last 4 numbers of the card number or account number
                • settled string Description: Whether or not the tranaction has been settled. Possible response values are `0` or `1`
                • settled_amount undefined Description: The settled amount
                • settled_date undefined Description: The date when the transaction was settled
                • ip_address string Description: The ip address recorded that requested the transaction (if applicable)
              cURL JavaScript Node Python

  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/transaction/{id} \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82' \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980'
              fetch('https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/payment/transaction/{id}', { 
    method: 'GET', 
    headers: {
        "Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82",

    console.log('Request failed', error);

              List Payment Transactions

              List payment transactions and filter by parameters


              get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/transactions Try Out

              • Request
              • Response
              • Coding

              query

              transaction_id OPTIONAL

              string

              Search by transaction_id.

              Separate multiple transaction_id's with a comma.

              Example: "8766546353263, 865756353537"

              start_date OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for transactions beginning on a particular date.

              Format date as a mm/dd/yy string.

              Example: "01/01/18"

              end_date OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for transactions ending on a particular date.

              Format date as a mm/dd/yy string.

              Example: "04/01/18"

              payment_type OPTIONAL

              string

              A case-sensitive string to return transactions by specific payment type type.

              * cc = Credit Card transactions
              * ach = ACH Transactions

              You can return both cc and ach transactions by separating the values with a comma.

              Example: "cc, ach"

              trxn_status OPTIONAL

              string

              A case-sensitive string to return transactions by specific status type

              * `approved` = Approved transactions
              * `declined` = Declined transactions

              amount OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for a specific amount.

              Use whole numbers and up to two decimals as necessary.

              * Example: $12.00 = `"12"` or `12.0` or `"12.00"`
              * Example: $18.40 = `18.4` or `"18.40"`
              * Example: $48.98 = `"48.98"`

              amount_from OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for a "from amount" to return all transactions equal to or greater than value entered.

              Use whole numbers and up to two decimals as necessary.

              * Example: $12.00 = `"12"` or `12.0` or `"12.00"`
              * Example: $18.40 = `18.4` or `"18.40"`
              * Example: $48.98 = `"48.98"`

              cardholder_name OPTIONAL

              string

              Case sensitive string search for transactions by name on credit card. Partial matches will be returned.

              EXAMPLE: sending `Jer` will return transactions with `cardholder_name` Jerry Simms and also Brenda Jerkins

              card_brand OPTIONAL

              string

              Case sensitive string search for transactions by card brand.

              Valid values are:
              * `visa`
              * `mastercard`
              * `amex`
              * `discover`
              * `jcb`
              * `diners``

              You can return multiple specific card brand combinations by separating the card brand names with a comma.

              * Example: `"visa, amex"`

              order_id OPTIONAL

              string

              Case sensitive string search for transactions by `order_id`.

              You can return multiple transactions by separating the order_id with a comma.

              * Example: `"abc-1277645, abc-1387665"`

              first_6 OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for transactions matching the first 6 digits of credit card account numbers.

              You can return multiple transactions by separating the first_6 with a comma.

              * Example: `"545454, 454847"`

              last_4 OPTIONAL

              string

              Search for transactions matching the last 4 digits of credit card account numbers.

              You can return multiple transactions by separating the last_4 with a comma.

              Example: `"4766, 1287"`

              limit OPTIONAL

              string

              The number of results to return when viewing a page.

              The default limit is 40

              offset OPTIONAL

              string

              The number of results to skip before returning results.

              The default offset is 0

              header

              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: T6554252567241061980

              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

              string

              Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

              The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

              **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

              200

              Example Value | Model 

              {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "count": "",
        "limit": "",
        "offset": "",
        "transactions": [
            {
                "trxn_status": "",
                "trxn_date": "",
                "trxn_type": "",
                "trxn_id": "",
                "cardholder_name": "",
                "card_type": "",
                "amount": "",
                "order_id": "",
                "authcode": "",
                "avs_code": "",
                "cv_code": "",
                "first_6": "",
                "last_4": "",
                "settled": "",
                "settled_amount": "",
                "settled_date": ""
            }
        ]
    }
}
              • status * string
              • code * string
              • message * string
              • data object
                • count integer
                • limit integer
                • offset integer
                  • trxn_status string
                  • trxn_date string
                  • trxn_type string
                  • trxn_id string
                  • cardholder_name string
                  • card_type string
                  • amount string
                  • order_id string
                  • authcode string
                  • avs_code string
                  • cv_code string
                  • first_6 string
                  • last_4 string
                  • settled string

                string

                The number of results to skip before returning results.

                For example, setting an offset of 20 means that the API will discard the first 20 results.

                200

                Example Value | Model

                  List Proof of Delivery (POD) records

                  Query for Proof of Delivery (POD) / Service records


                  get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/transaction/proof_of_delivery/ Try Out

                  • Request
                  • Response
                  • Coding

                  query

                  pofs_id OPTIONAL

                  string

                  The POD unique identifier. Begins with `pofs-`

                  trxn_id OPTIONAL

                  string

                  The unique transaction identifier associated to this POD.

                  Separate multiple `trxn_id` as a string with commas. Example: `"98773837463622, 9837343243822`

                  shipper OPTIONAL

                  integer

                  Query POD by shipper. Values are:

                  * `1` = USPS
                  * `2` = FedEx
                  * `3` = UPS
                  * `4` = DHL
                  * `5` = Other

                  tracking_no OPTIONAL

                  string

                  The shipper tracking number to this POD

                  delivery_date OPTIONAL

                  string

                  The delivery date associated to this POD. Format is `YYYY-MM-DD`.

                  Query multiple delivery dates in a string separated by a comma.

                  Example `"2019-05-05, 2019-05-06"`

                  header

                  Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                  string

                  Default: T6554252567241061980

                  The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                  NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                  Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                  string

                  Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                  The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                  **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                  200

                  Example Value | Model 

                  {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": [
        {
            "id": "",
            "trxn_id": "",
            "shipper": "",
            "tracking_no": "",
            "delivery_date": "",
            "modified": "",
            "created": ""
        }
    ]
}
                  • status string
                  • code string
                  • message string
                    • id string Description: The Proof of Delivery / Service ID
                    • trxn_id string Description: The transaction ID assocaited with the POD
                    • shipper integer Description: The shipper associated with the Proof of Delivery. * `1` = USPS * `2` = FedEx * `3` = UPS * `4` = DHL * `5` = Other
                    • tracking_no string Description: The shipper tracking number associated to this POD
                    • delivery_date string Description: The delivery date assocaited with to this POD
                    • modified string
                    • created string

                  Refleqtion

                  Import transactions and their corresponding results

                  Refleqtion is intended to allow the ISV / Merchant supply transactions and their corresponding results that have been processed by an external processor


                  post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /refleqtion Try Out

                  • Request
                  • Response
                  • Coding

                  header

                  Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                  string

                  Default: T6554252567241061980

                  The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                  NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                  Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                  string

                  Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                  The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                  **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                  body

                  body OPTIONAL

                  Example Value | Model 

                  {
    "type": "",
    "mid": "",
    "transaction_data": {
        "orderid": "",
        "amount": "",
        "service_charge": "",
        "currency": "USD",
        "cfirstname": "",
        "clastname": "",
        "cemail": "",
        "cphone": "",
        "ipaddress": ""
    },
    "payment": {
        "cardfullname": "",
        "first_6": "",
        "last_4": "",
        "month": "",
        "year": "",
        "cvv": "",
        "store_payment": false
    },
    "items": [
        {
            "name": "",
            "description": "",
            "ucc": "",
            "upc": "",
            "unit_price": 0,
            "units_sold": 0,
            "unit_measurement": "",
            "total_amount": ""
        },
        {
            "name": "",
            "description": "",
            "ucc": " ",
            "upc": "",
            "unit_price": 0,
            "units_sold": 0,
            "unit_measurement": "",
            "total_amount": ""
        }
    ]
}
                  • type * string Enum: Description: the transaction type
                  • mid * string Description: the merchant id (MID) assigned by QorPay or your merchant service provider (MSP)
                  • auto_settle * integer
                  • transaction_data * object
                    • status string Description: status of the transaction - `approved` or `declined`
                    • authcode string Description: if transaction was `approved` supply the authorization code from the processor
                    • denial_code string Description: if transaction was `declined` supply the denial code from the processor
                    • denial_code_description string Description: if transaction was `declined` supply the denial code description from the processor
                    • orderid * string Description: unique merchant order number
                    • invoiceid string Description: merchant invoice number
                    • transaction_date string
                    • transaction_id string Description: the processors / merchants unique transaction id, that is used in the corresponding settlement file
                    • reference_id string Description: A reference id that will be echo'd back in the message response.
                    • transaction_type string Enum: Description: to further define the transaction type Potential values are `cc` = credit card, `debit` = PIN debit, `ebt` = electronic benefits, 'gc' = gift card, `voy` = voyager, `wex` = wright express
                    • entry_mode string Enum: Description: how was the credit/debit card entered
                    • amount * string Description: the total amount to process
                    • service_charge string Description: the amount of the total sum of this transaction that is made up of the service charge
                    • currency string Description: the currency to process. Defaults to `USD` if no value provided
                    • mcc_code string Description: The Merchant Category Code )MCC) for the merchant of record
                    • cfirstname string Description: the customer's first name
                    • clastname string Description: the customer's last name
                    • cemail string Description: the customer's email address
                    • cphone string Description: the customer's phone number
                    • ipaddress string Description: the IP address of the client or server sending the request
                  • payment object
                    • cardfullname string Description: the name printed or embossed on the front of the credit/debit card `required` if store payment is set to true
                    • name_on_account string Description: the name of the account holder for bank accounts (ach) or crypto accounts
                    • routing_number string Description: if type = `ach`, then supply the routing number for the bank account
                    • account_number string Description: the credit/debit card or bank account number. If you do not have the full account number then `first_6` and `last_4` are required.
                    • first_6 string Description: The first 6 digits of the credit/debit card (BIN) or bank account number
                    • last_4 string Description: The last 4 digits of the credit/debit card or bank account number
                    • month string Description: the card expiration month - as 2 digits (ex. `02` for Febuary)
                    • year string Description: the card expiration year - as 2 digits (ex. `24` for 2024)
                    • cvv string Description: the credit/debit card verification value. 3 digits for Visa, MasterCard, Discover 4 digits for American Express
                    • store_payment boolean Description: if set to `true`, this will store payment information in the QorCommerce Vault and return a payment token `account_number` is required along with the expiration date for a credit/debit cards, `routing_number` and name_on_account are required for bank accounts
                  • billing object
                    • bzip string Description: the customer's billing zip code `required` if transaction is a credit/debit card
                    • bcountry string Description: the customer's billing country code
                    • baddress string Description: the customer's billing street address
                    • baddress2 string Description: the customer's billing street address 2
                    • bcity string Description: the customer's billing city
                    • bstate string Description: the customer's billing state code - as 2 characters (ex. FL)
                  • shipping object
                    • scountry string Description: the shipping address country code - as 3 characters (ex. `USA`)
                    • saddress string Description: the shipping street address
                    • saddress2 string Description: the shipping street address 2
                    • scity string Description: the shipping city
                    • sstate string Description: the shipping state code - as 2 characters (ex. FL)
                    • szip integer Description: the shipping zip/postal code
                    • sphone integer Description: the shipping phone number (no dashes, hyphens, specail characters)
                    • name string Description: the name of the item
                    • description string Description: a description of the item
                    • ucc string Description: the item's Universal Commercial Code
                    • upc string Description: the item's Universal Product Code
                    • unit_price integer Description: the price per unit for the item
                    • units_sold integer Description: the number of item units sold
                    • unit_measurement string Description: the unit of measurement
                    • total_amount string Description: the total amount of the item sale which should equal unit_price * units_sold + any taxes, discounts and/or fees
                  • threeDS object
                    • response_3DS string Description: Status response from 3-D Secure provider. Possible values are typically `success`, `failure`, `noaction` or `error` but can vary depending on provider
                    • CAVV string Description: The 3-D Secure Cardholder Authentication Verification Value (MasterCardâs UCAF value)
                    • ECIFlag integer Description: Electronic Commerce Indicator `0` = Payment has been flagged as SSL secured transaction `1` = Payment has been flagged as SSL 3-D Secure authentication transaction (cardholder enrolled) `2` = Payment has been flagged as SSL 3-D Secure authentication transaction (cardholder not enrolled or partial authenticated)
                    • XID string Description: 3-D Secure Transaction Identifier
                  • risk object
                    • risk_provider string Description: the risk management provider
                    • risk_score integer Description: the risk score associated to this transaction (if you are using a risk prevention system)
                  201

                  Example Value | Model 

                  {
    "status": "approved",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Refleqtion request recorded successfully",
    "transaction_date": "2020-11-03 07:13:55",
    "transaction_id": "831649658996418",
    "amount_recorded": "15.00",
    "order_id": "oid_1tES2kggOe",
    "authcode": "B12301"
}
                  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `approved` and `error` Example: approved
                  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
                  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Refleqtion request recorded successfully
                  • transaction_date string Description: The date and time that the transaction took place Example: 2020-11-03 07:13:55
                  • transaction_id string Description: The unique transaction identifier echo'd from request. Example: 831649658996418
                  • amount_recorded string Description: The total amount recorded Example: 15.00
                  • order_id string Description: The unique Order ID for this transaction Example: oid_1tES2kggOe
                  • authcode string Description: The authorization code of the transaction. If the transaction is a `sale` or `authorization` approval Example: B12301

                      List Customers

                      Fetch a list of customers


                      get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /customers Try Out

                      • Request
                      • Response
                      • Coding

                      query

                      cust_id OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Search for customer by `id`. Separate multiple id filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `635, 732`

                      first_name OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by first name. Separate multiple first_name filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"James, Sally, Mitch"`

                      last_name OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by last name. Separate multiple last_name filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"Brown, O'Brein, Contenelli"`

                      address OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by street address. Partial input allowed.

                      **Example:** `Main` will return all customers that have **Main** in their street address.

                      address2 OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by second street address. Partial input allowed.

                      **Example:** `Apt` will return all customers that have **Apt** in their secondary street address.

                      city OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by city name. Separate multiple city name filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"Los Angeles, Miami, Lake Arrowhead"`

                      state OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by ISO 2-digit state code. Separate multiple state code filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example, `"CA, MN, GA"`

                      zip OPTIONAL

                      string

                      customer address zip code

                      country OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by ISO 2-digit country code. Separate multiple country code filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"US, CA, RD"`

                      email OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by email address. Partial input allowed. For example, `example.com` will return all customers that have **example.com** in their email address. Separate multiple email filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"example.com, sally@company.com, .net"`

                      phone_number OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by phone number. Partial input allowed.

                      **Example:** `213` will return all customers that have **213** in their phone number

                      company_name OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by company name. Partial matches provided. For example, `bro` will return all customers that have **bro** in their their company name. Separate multiple company_name filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"bro, Acme Plumbing, Hatfield & McCoy"`

                      web_address OPTIONAL

                      string

                      Case-insensitive search for customers by website address. Partial matches provided. For example, `jan` will return all customers that have **jan** in their their website address. Separate multiple web_address filters with a `,` (comma).

                      **Example:** `"jan, example.com"`

                          List Plans

                          List plans and filter by parameters


                          get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /plans Try Out

                          • Request
                          • Response
                          • Coding

                          query

                          plan_id OPTIONAL

                          string

                          Provide the contract plan_id. Separate multiple plans with a comma.

                          **Example:**
                          * `plan_1`
                          * `plan_1,plan_2,plan_3`

                          card_fullname OPTIONAL

                          string

                          provide the the full name provided on the card associated with this plan

                          last_4 OPTIONAL

                          string

                          Provide the last 4 numbers of the card associated with a plan.

                          amount OPTIONAL

                          string

                          Provide the amount charged per payment period for the plan.

                          header

                          Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                          string

                          Default: T6554252567241061980

                          The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                          NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                          Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                          string

                          Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                          The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                          **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                          201

                          Example Value | Model 

                          {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "count": "",
        "limit": "",
        "offset": "",
        "plans": [
            {
                "plan_id": "",
                "created": "",
                "last_run": "",
                "trxn_count": "",
                "card_fullname": "",
                "last_4": "",
                "plan_start": "",
                "plan_end": "",
                "period": "",
                "amount": ""
            }
        ]
    }
}
                          • status * string
                          • code * string
                          • message * string
                          • data object
                            • count integer
                            • limit integer
                            • offset integer
                              • plan_id string
                              • created string
                              • last_run string
                              • trxn_count integer
                              • card_fullname string
                              • last_4 string
                              • plan_start string
                              • plan_end string
                              • period string
                              • amount number

                            Disputes

                            Fetch Disputes

                            A dispute occurs when a customer questions your charge with their card issuer. When this happens, you're given the opportunity to respond to the dispute with evidence that shows that the charge is legitimate


                            get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/disputes Try Out

                            • Request
                            • Response
                            • Coding

                            query

                            show_trxns OPTIONAL

                            integer

                            Indicates whether or not to show the original transactions associated to each dispute.

                            status OPTIONAL

                            string

                            Indicates which specific status the request will search for.

                            Possible request values are `open`, `closed`, `won` or `lost`

                            Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                            string

                            Default: T6554252567241061980

                            • Response

                            Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                            string

                            NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                            Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                            string

                            Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                            The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                            **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                            body

                            body OPTIONAL

                            Example Value | Model 

                            {
    "transaction_data": {
        "mid": "",
        "name": "",
        "uri": "",
        "event": "",
        "content_type": "",
        "header_key": "",
        "header_value": ""
    }
}
                            • transaction_data * object
                              • mid * string Description: The merchant id (MID) assigned by <> or your merchant service provider (MSP).
                              • name * string Description: Name of your event
                              • uri * string Description: The uri that will receive the webhook message
                              • event * string Enum: Description: Webhook event (see below)
                              • content_type string Enum:
                              • header_key string
                              • header_value string
                            201

                            Example Value | Model 

                            {
    "status": "ok",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Webhook successfully created",
    "id": "hook_af67a911391711e9924d0afd24307790"
}

                            • code string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
                            • message string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Webhook successfully created
                            • id string Description: The webhook id of the created event Example: hook_af67a911391711e9924d0afd24307790

                              Create a Payment Form (linq)

                              post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /payment/linq Try Out

                              • Request
                              • Response
                              • Coding

                              header

                              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: T6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                              The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                              **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                              body

                              body OPTIONAL

                              Example Value | Model 

                              {
    "transaction_data": {}
}
                              • transaction_data * object
                                • mid * string Description: the merchant id assigned by QorCommerce or your merchant service provider (MSP)
                                • form_id * string Description: Form template id you would like to use from the **Get Payment Forms Linq** endpoint
                                • description * string Description: Description for this order. If left blank, this will be left off the form
                                • expires integer Description: Expiration time for this linq. Possible values are 1 day (86400), 1 week (604800) or 1 month (2592000) or a time in seconds of your choice
                                • amount * string Description: The total amount to process
                                • order_id string Description: Unique merchant order tracking number
                                • po_number string Description: Unique purchase order tracking number
                                • via string Enum: Description: Whether you intend to send this linq via `SMS` or `Email`
                              201

                              {
    "status": "ok",
    "code": "GW00",
    "message": "Payment Linq successfully created",
    "data": "https://...",
    "request_id": "req_..."
}
                              • status string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` or `error` Example: ok
                              • code string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail. Example: GW00
                              • message string Description: A payment gateway status code message. Example: Payment Linq successfully created
                              • data string Description: The http link for this payment form that you can send to a customer for online payment Example: https://...
                              • request_id string Description: The request id for this payment form - this is used in the **Send Payment Form Linq** endpoint Example: req_...
