                              Channels > ISV / Referrer / MarketPlace

                              New Merchant - (Sign Up / Enrollment)

                              Add / Enroll a new Merchant to your portfolio


                              post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/new_merchant Try Out

                              • Request
                              • Response
                              • Coding

                              header

                              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: T6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: C6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the channel making this request.

                              body

                              body OPTIONAL

                              Example Value | Model

                              {
    "data": {
        "descriptor": "Smith Processing",
        "annualCCSales": 1000000,
        "avgTicket": 10000,
        "environment": "retail",
        "mcc": "8111",
        "merchant": {
            "type": 0,
            "name": "Smith Company LLC",
            "address1": "123 North 12 St",
            "address2": "Suite 403",
            "city": "Miami",
            "state": "FL",
            "zip": 33024,
            "country": "USA",
            "timezone": "est",
            "phone": 1234567891,
            "email": "support@example.com",
            "ein": 123456789,
            "website": "http://www.example.comt",
            "locations": 1,
            "public": 1,
            "bank_accounts": [
                {
                    "account": {
                        "method": 8,
                        "number": "023456789012345",
                        "routing": "063013924"
                    },
                    "currency": "USD",
                    "primary": 1
                }
            ]
        },
        "owners": [
            {
                "title": "CEO",
                "first": "James",
                "last": "Smith",
                "dob": 19590122,
                "email": "james.smith@example.com",
                "ownership": 8000,
                "timezone": "est",
                "address1": "123 Example St.",
                "address2": "Suite 403",
                "city": "Miami",
                "state": "FL",
                "zip": 33024,
                "country": "USA",
                "phone": 1234567891,
                "ssn": 123456789,
                "primary": 1
            }
        ]
    }
}
                              • data * object
                                • descriptor * string Description: The name under which the merchant is doing business.
                                • annualCCSales * integer Description: The value of annual credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'
                                • avgTicket * integer Description: The value of average credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'
                                • environment * string Description: The environment the merchant is in. Possible request values are `retail`, `moto`, `supermarket`, `cardPresent`, `restaurant`, `serviceStation`, `fuel` and `ecommerce`
                                • mcc * string Description: The Merchant Category Code of this merchant. Contact dev ops for proper codes
                                • merchant * object
                                  • type * integer Description: The type of merchant that this merchant is. Possible request values are `0`(Sole Proprietor), `1`(Corporation), `2`(Limited Liability Company), `3`(Partnership), `5`(Non-Profit Organization) and `6`(Government Organization)
                                  • name * string Description: The name of this merchant.
                                  • address1 * string Description: The first line of the address associated with this merchant.
                                  • address2 string Description: The second line of the address associated with this merchant.
                                  • city * string Description: The city associated with this merchant.
                                  • state * string Description: The state associated with this merchant. Must be the state's two letter abbreviation
                                  • zip * integer Description: The zip code associated with this merchant.
                                  • country * string Description: The country associated with this merchant. Currently only accepts `USA`
                                  • timezone * string Description: The timezone associated with this merchant. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`
                                  • phone * integer Description: The phone number associated with this merchant.
                                  • email * string Description: The email associated with this merchant.
                                  • ein * integer Description: The IRS Employer Number associated with this merchant.
                                  • website * string Description: The website url associated with this merchant.
                                  • locations * integer Description: The number of locations this merchant has.
                                  • public * integer Description: Indicates whether or not this merchant is publicly held.
                                    • account * object
                                      • method * integer Description: this account's type. Possible request values are `8`(Checking), `9`(Savings), `10`(Corporate Checking) and `11`(Corporate Savings)
                                      • number * string Description: The bank number of this account.
                                      • routing * string Description: The routing number of this account.
                                    • currency * string Description: The currency type this merchant is using. Only accepts `USD`
                                    • primary * integer Description: Indicates whether or not this account is the primary account of this merchant. Possible request values are `0` and `1`
                                • title * string Description: The title for this owner.
                                • first * string Description: The first name of this owner.
                                • last * string Description: The last name of this owner.
                                • dob * integer Description: The date of birth of this owner. The field is in the form `YYYYMMDD`
                                • email * string Description: The email associated with this owner.
                                • ownership * integer Description: The percent ownership that this owner has. The field is represented as basis points, so 80% would be 8000
                                • timezone * string Description: The timezone associated with this owner. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`
                                • address1 * string Description: The first line of the address associated with this owner.
                                • address2 string Description: The second line address associated with this owner.
                                • city * string Description: The city associated with this owner.

                              New MarketPlace Merchant - (Sign Up / Enrollment)

                              Add / Enroll a new MarketPlace Merchant to your portfolio


                              post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/new_marketplace_merchant Try Out

                              • Request
                              • Response
                              • Coding

                              header

                              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: T6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: C6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the channel making this request.

                              body

                              body OPTIONAL

                              Example Value | Model

}
                              • data * object
                                • descriptor * string Description: The name under which the merchant is doing business.
                                • annualCCSales integer Description: The value of annual credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'
                                • avgTicket integer Description: The value of average credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'
                                • mcc string Description: The Merchant Category Code of this merchant. Contact dev ops for proper codes
                                • merchant * object
                                  • type * integer Description: The type of merchant that this merchant is. Possible request values are `0`(Sole Proprietor), `1`(Corporation), `2`(Limited Liability Company), `3`(Partnership), `5`(Non-Profit Organization) and `6`(Government Organization)
                                  • name * string Description: The name of this merchant.
                                  • address1 * string Description: The first line of the address associated with this merchant.
                                  • address2 string Description: The second line of the address associated with this merchant.
                                  • city * string Description: The city associated with this merchant.
                                  • state * string Description: The state associated with this merchant. Must be the state's two letter abbreviation
                                  • zip * integer Description: The zip code associated with this merchant.
                                  • country * string Description: The country associated with this merchant. Currently only accepts `USA`
                                  • timezone * string Description: The timezone associated with this merchant. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`
                                  • phone * integer Description: The phone number associated with this merchant.
                                  • email * string Description: The email associated with this merchant.
                                  • ein * integer Description: The IRS Employer Number / SSN associated with this merchant.
                                    • account * object
                                      • method * integer Description: this account's type. Possible request values are `8`(Checking), `9`(Savings), `10`(Corporate Checking) and `11`(Corporate Savings)
                                      • number * string Description: The bank number of this account.
                                      • routing * string Description: The routing number of this account.
                                    • currency * string Description: The currency type this merchant is using. Only accepts `USD`
                                    • primary * integer Description: Indicates whether or not this account is the primary account of this merchant. Possible request values are `0` and `1`
                                • title * string Description: The title for this owner.
                                • first * string Description: The first name of this owner.
                                • last * string Description: The last name of this owner.
                                • dob * integer Description: The date of birth of this owner. The field is in the form `YYYYMMDD`
                                • email * string Description: The email associated with this owner.
                                • ownership * integer Description: The percent ownership that this owner has. The field is represented as basis points, so 80% would be 8000
                                • timezone * string Description: The timezone associated with this owner. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`
                                • address1 * string Description: The first line of the address associated with this owner.
                                • address2 string Description: The second line address associated with this owner.
                                • city * string Description: The city associated with this owner.
                                • state * string Description: The state associated with this owner. Must be the state's two letter abbreviation
                                • zip * integer Description: The zip code associated with this owner.
                                • country * string Description: The country associated with this owner. Currently only accepts `USA`
                                • phone * integer Description: The phone number associated with this owner.
                                • ssn * integer Description: The social security code of this owner.
                                • primary * integer Description: Indicates whether or not this is the primary owner.
                              200

    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "id": ""

                              Fetch Merchant Status

                              Fetch the Merchant Status and return the Merchant Credentials / Merchant ID (MID) if it has been boarded


                              get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/merchant_status/{id} Try Out

                              • Request
                              • Response
                              • Coding

                              header

                              Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: T6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                              NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                              Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                              string

                              Default: C6554252567241061980

                              The unique key identifying the channel making this request.

                              200

                              Example Value | Model 

                              {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "company_name": "",
        "account_type": "",
        "integration_type": "",
        "mer_id": "",
        "app_key": "",
        "client_key": "",
        "mid": "",
        "monthly_charge_limit": "",
        "max_transaction_amount": "",
        "status": "",
        "boarded": "",
        "is_payfac": "",
        "created": ""
    }
}
                              • status * string Description: The status of the request. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                              • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.
                              • message * string Description: A status code message.
                              • data object
                                • company_name string Description: The company name on the account
                                • account_type string Description: The account type / environment
                                • integration_type string Description: The application that has integrated to <> payment platform
                                • mer_id string Description: The unique <> id
                                • app_key string Description: The Qor-App-Key credentials
                                • client_key string Description: The Qor-Client-Key credentials
                                • mid string Description: The assigned Merchant ID (MID) for the account
                                • monthly_charge_limit string Description: The monthly volume limit that the merchant is allowed to charge
                                • max_transaction_amount string Description: The maximum amount that a merchant is allowed to charge per transaction
                                • status string Description: The current account status. Possible response values are `active`, `pending`, `terminated`, `refund pending`, `refund only`, and `data view only`
                                • boarded integer Description: Has the account been boarded. Possible response values are 0 = `no` and 1 = `yes`
                                • is_payfac integer Description: Whether are not this account has been boarded under the PayFac status
                                • created string Description: The creation date of the account

                                Fetch My Merchants

                                Fetch your portfolio of merchants


                                get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/my_merchants Try Out

                                • Request
                                • Response
                                • Coding

                                query

                                mer_id OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The merchant ID of the specific account being searched for.

                                account_type OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The account type of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Possible request value are `ecomm`, `retail` and `moto`

                                company OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The name of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The company field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                address OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The first line of the address of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The address field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                address2 OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The second line of the address of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The address2 field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                city OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The city of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The city field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                state OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The state of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The state field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                zip OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The zip code of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The zip code field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                webaddress OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The web address of the merchent(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The web address field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                firstname OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The first name of the contact of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The firstname field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                lastname OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The last name of the contact of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The lastname field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                phone OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The phone number of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Note: The phone field does not have to be completed to perform a search

                                api_login OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The api login of the merchant that is being searched for.

                                status OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The status of the merchant(s) that are being searched for.

                                Possible request values are `1` = Active, `2` = Pending, `3` = Suspended, `4` = Terminated, `5` = Refund Pending and `6` = Terminated (Refunds)

                                limit OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The amount of marchants that will be shown in a single response.

                                The highest amount allowed for the limit is `250`

                                offset OPTIONAL

                                string

                                The offset of the given response.

                                header

                                Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                string

                                Default: T6554252567241061980

                                The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                string

                                Default: C6554252567241061980

                                The unique key identifying the channel making this request.

                                200

                                • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                                • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.

                                • data object
                                  • total integer Description: The total number of merchants associated with this specific referrer.

                                    • last_activity string Description: The date of this merchant's last activity.
                                    • status string Description: The status of this specific merchant.
                                    • is_inactive integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule is inactive. Possible response values are `0` and `1`
                                    • total_disbursements integer Description: The total number of deposits this specific merchant has had.
                                    • first_disbursement string Description: The date of the first disbursement of this specific merchant.
                                    • funds object
                                      • available string Description: The amount that is marked as available funds.
                                      • total string Description: The amount of total funds a merchant has.
                                      • reserved string Description: The amount held as reserved funds
                                      • pending string Description: The amount that is marked as pending funds.

                                Clone a payment form and/or receipt

                                Clone a payment form and/or receipt


                                post https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/clone/payment_form Try Out

                                • Request
                                • Response
                                • Coding

                                header

                                Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                string

                                Default: T6554252567241061980

                                The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                string

                                Default: C6554252567241061980

                                The unique key identifying the channel making this request.

                                body

                                body OPTIONAL

                                Example Value | Model

                                {
    "client_key": "",
    "name": "",
    "autorefunds": "",
    "receipt_img": "",
    "merchant_logo": "",
    "receipt_id": "",
    "payment_form_id": "",
    "subject": "",
    "from_name": "",
    "replyto": "",
    "replyto_name": "",
    "payment_form_message": "",
    "receipt_title": "",
    "receipt_footer": "",
    "receipt_greeting": ""
}
                                • form object
                                  • client_key_from * string Description: Client key to copy forms and receipts from
                                  • client_key_to * string Description: Assigned client key to clone forms and receipts to
                                  • merchant_id_to * string Description: Assigned merchant id (MID) for the client_key_to.
                                  • payment_form_name string Description: Name for the cloned form. If left blank or omitted the new form is set to the original
                                  • receipt_name string Description: Name for the cloned receipt. If left blank or omitted the new receipt is set to the original
                                  • receipt_img string Description: URL of an image that will be used
                                  • merchant_logo string Description: URL of an image that will be used
                                  • receipt_id * string Description: The receipt id that you want cloned. Include with a payment_form_id to copy and attach to that payment form
                                  • payment_form_id * string Description: the form id that you want cloned. Not required when only cloning a receipt
                                  • subject string Description: The Subject line on the email
                                  • from_name string Description: The From for emails
                                  • replyto string Description: The Reply-To for emails
                                  • replyto_name string Description: The Reply-to name for emails
                                  • payment_form_message string Description: The message that you would like to have on a payment form
                                  • receipt_title string Description: The title you would like on a receipt
                                  • receipt_footer string Description: The footer you would like on a receipt
                                  • receipt_greeting string Description: The greeting you would like on a receipt
                                200

                                Example Value | Model

                                {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "for_account_name": "",
    "form_id": "",
    "receipt_id": ""
}
                                • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                                • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.
                                • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message.
                                • for_account_name string Description: The name of the merchant that the new form and/or receipts were created.
                                • form_id string Description: The new form id if available.
                                • receipt_id string Description: The new receipt id if available.
                                cURL JavaScript Node Python

                                  Fetch a Merchant's bank account(s) information


                                  get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/bank_accounts Try Out

                                  • Request
                                  • Response
                                  • Coding

                                  header

                                  Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                  string

                                  Default: T6554252567241061980

                                  The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                  NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                  Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                  string

                                  Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                                  The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                                  **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                                  200

                                  Example Value | Model 

                                  {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "count": "",
        "bank_accounts": [
            {
                "created": "",
                "id": "",
                "number": "",
                "routing": "",
                "method": "",
                "is_primary": "",
                "status": "",
                "is_inactive": "",
                "is_frozen": "",
                "type": "",
                "reserved": ""
            }
        ]
    }
}
                                  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                                  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.
                                  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message.
                                  • data object
                                    • count integer Description: The total number of bank accounts present in this response.
                                      • created string Description: The date that this specific bank account was created.
                                      • id string Description: The ID of this specific bank account.
                                      • number string Description: The last four digits of the card number associated with this specific bank account.
                                      • routing string Description: The last four digits of the routing number associated with this specific bank accounts
                                      • method string Description: The type of this specific bank account.
                                      • is_primary integer Description: Indicator of whether or not this is the primary bank account. Possible response values are `0` and `1`
                                      • status string Description: The status of this specific bank account.
                                      • is_inactive integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule is inactive. Possible response values are `0` and `1`
                                      • is_frozen integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule is frozen. Possible response values are `0` and `1`
                                      • type string Description: The type of account that this specific bank account is. Possible response values are `all`, `debit` and `credit`
                                      • reserved string Description: Indicates whether or not the bank account is reserved and what action will take place if so.
                                  cURL JavaScript Node Python 
                                  curl --request GET \
  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/channels/bank_accounts \
  --header 'Qor-App-Key: T6554252567241061980' \
  --header 'Qor-Client-Key: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82'
                                  fetch('https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/channels/bank_accounts', { 
    method: 'GET', 
    headers: {
        "Qor-App-Key": "T6554252567241061980",
        "Qor-Client-Key": "01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82"
    }, 
}) 
.then(e => e.json()) 
.then((data) => { 
    console.log('Request succeeded with JSON response', data); 
}) 
.catch((error) => { 
    console.log('Request failed', error); 
});

                                  Fetch Settlement Schedule(s)

                                  Fetch a Merchant's settlement schedule(s).


                                  get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/settlement Try Out

                                  • Request
                                  • Response
                                  • Coding

                                  header

                                  Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                  string

                                  Default: T6554252567241061980

                                  The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                  NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                  Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                  string

                                  Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                                  The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                                  **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                                  200

                                  Example Value | Model 

                                  {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "count": "",
        "withdrawals": [
            {
                "created": "",
                "id": "",
                "schedule": "",
                "schedule_factor": "",
                "start_date": "",
                "unit_of_measure": "",
                "amount": "",
                "minimum": "",
                "maximum": "",
                "float": "",
                "skip_off_days": "",
                "is_inactive": "",
                "is_frozen": "",
                "is_same_day": ""
            }
        ]
    }
}
                                  • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                                  • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.
                                  • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message.
                                  • data object
                                    • count integer Description: The total number of withdrawals present in this response.
                                      • created string Description: The date that this withdrawal was created.
                                      • id string Description: The ID of this specifc withdrawal.
                                      • schedule string Description: The schedule at which how frequently the withdrawal is executed.
                                      • schedule_factor integer Description: The factor that the schedule is mulitplied by.
                                      • start_date integer Description: The date that the withdrawal schedule will start.
                                      • unit_of_measure integer Description: The percent of how much will be withdrawn when a withdrawal is executed.
                                      • amount string Description: The total amount of this withdrawal.
                                      • minimum string Description: The minimum amount that must be met before a withdrawal is performed.
                                      • maximum string Description: The maximum amount that this withdrawal will be.
                                      • float integer Description: The minimum amount that an account wants to maintain.
                                      • skip_off_days integer Description: Option that skips withdrawals on holidays and weekends.
                                      • is_inactive integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule is inactive.
                                      • is_frozen integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule is frozen.
                                      • is_same_day integer Description: Indicates whether or not this withdrawal schedule executes on the same day it is created.
                                  cURL JavaScript Node Python

  --url https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3/channels/settlement \

                                    Fetch Deposits / Payouts

                                    Fetch all deposits / payouts for a merchant.


                                    get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/deposits/{year}/{status} Try Out

                                    • Request
                                    • Response
                                    • Coding

                                    query

                                    limit OPTIONAL

                                    integer

                                    The amount of deposits present on one page. The maximum amount is 100. The default is 100.

                                    skip OPTIONAL

                                    integer

                                    The page number that the response will start at.
                                    The default is 0

                                    created OPTIONAL

                                    integer

                                    The date that the request is searching for.

                                    The request field will be in the form `YYYYMMDD`

                                    amount OPTIONAL

                                    number

                                    The amount that the request is searching for.

                                    header

                                    Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                    string

                                    Default: T6554252567241061980

                                    The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                    NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                    Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                    string

                                    Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                                    The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                                    **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                                    200

                                    Example Value | Model

                                    Fetch Disputes

                                    List a Merchant's disputes.


                                    get https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3 /channels/disputes Try Out

                                    • Request
                                    • Response
                                    • Coding

                                    query

                                    show_trxns OPTIONAL

                                    integer

                                    Indicates whether or not to show the original transactions associated to each dispute.

                                    Possible request values are `0` or `1`

                                    status OPTIONAL

                                    string

                                    Indicates which specific status the request will search for.

                                    Possible request values are `open`, `closed`, `won` or `lost`

                                    header

                                    Qor-App-Key REQUIRED

                                    string

                                    Default: T6554252567241061980

                                    The unique key identifying the app making this request.

                                    NOTE: If testing use **`T6554252567241061980`** for the **`Qor-App-Key`** header key.

                                    Qor-Client-Key REQUIRED

                                    string

                                    Default: 01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82

                                    The Client key represents an authorized **merchant account** and is assigned by <> or your merchant service account provider.

                                    **NOTE:** If testing use `01dffeb784c64d098c8c691ea589eb82 ` for the `Qor-Client-Key` header key.

                                    200

                                    Example Value | Model 

                                    {
    "status": "",
    "code": "",
    "message": "",
    "data": {
        "count": "",
        "total_disputes": "",
        "disputes": [
            {
                "dispute_id": "",
                "created": "",
                "cycle": "",
                "ARN": "",
                "status": "",
                "reason": "",
                "reason_description": "",
                "dispute_amount": "",
                "trxn_data": {
                    "trxn_id": "",
                    "trxn_date": "",
                    "trxn_amount": "",
                    "refunded_amount": "",
                    "card_number": "",
                    "avs": "",
                    "cvv": "",
                    "cardfullname": "",
                    "address1": "",
                    "address2": "",
                    "city": "",
                    "state": "",
                    "zip": "",
                    "email": "",
                    "phone": ""
                }
            }
        ]
    }
}
                                    • status * string Description: The status of the transaction. Possible response values are `ok` and `error`
                                    • code * string Description: See [Payment Response Codes](doc:payment-response-codes) for more detail.
                                    • message * string Description: A payment gateway status code message.
                                    • data object
                                      • count integer Description: The total amount of chargebacks present in this response.
                                      • total_disputes number Description: The sum amount of all the chargebacks in this response.
                                        • dispute_id string Description: The ID of this specific chrageback.
                                        • created string Description: The date that this chargeback was created.
                                        • cycle string Description: The currernt state that this chargeback is in.
                                        • ARN string Description: The issueing bank's refernce number for this chargeback.
                                        • status string Description: The current status of this chargeback.
                                        • reason string Description: The reason code for this chargeback.
                                        • reason_description string Description: The reason description for this chargeback.
                                        • dispute_amount string Description: The amount that this chargeback is disputing.
                                        • trxn_data object Description: The data of the original transaction that this chargeback is disputing.
                                          • trxn_id string Description: The ID of the original transaction.
                                          • trxn_date string Description: The date of the original transaction.
                                          • trxn_amount string Description: The amount of the original transaction.
                                          • refunded_amount string Description: The amount refunded if a refund has been issued.
                                          • card_number string Description: The masked card number used on the original transaction.
                                          • avs string Description: The avs response of this transaction if present, is `null` otherwise.
                                          • cvv string Description: The cvv response of this transaction if present, is `null` otherwise.
                                          • cardfullname string Description: The full name of the card holder that was used on the original transaction.
                                          • address1 string Description: The first line of the address associated with the original transaction.
                                          • address2 string Description: The second line of the address associated with the original transaction.
                                          • city string Description: The city associated with the original transaction.
                                          • state string Description: The state associated with the original transaction.
                                          • zip string Description: The zip code associated with the original transaction.
                                          • email string Description: The email associated with the original transaction.
                                          • phone string Description: The phone number associated with the original transaction.

                                      • sendto_email * string Description: the email address of the recipient
                                      • receipt_template_id string Description: the receipt template id that the merchant uses for their checkout & receipts (Styler). If omiitted the system will use the merchants default receipt template id to style the receipt.
                                      • transaction_type string Description: The transaction type of the approved `sale` or `refund`. Possible values are `sale` or `refund`. If omitted this defaults to `sale`.
